---
import Base from '../layouts/Base.astro';
---
<Base title="About — Paper Digest">
  <section class="hero" style="padding-bottom:12px;">
    <h1>About</h1>
  </section>
  <div class="basepair-divider" role="presentation"></div>

  <div class="summary" style="max-width:720px;">
    <section>
      <h2>What this is</h2>
      <p>
        An automated library of open-access bioinformatics research. A pipeline discovers strong
        papers across genomics, single-cell, proteomics, systems biology, computational methods and
        clinical informatics, reads each one in full, and writes a structured plain-language summary.
      </p>
    </section>
    <section>
      <h2>How the summaries are made</h2>
      <p>
        Each summary is written by an AI model from the paper's full text, then checked by a second
        model from a different family for faithfulness — an independent reviewer is more likely to
        catch mistakes than one sharing the first model's blind spots. High-confidence summaries
        publish automatically; anything flagged is held for human review.
      </p>
    </section>
    <section>
      <h2>Honesty about limits</h2>
      <p>
        AI checking AI catches most errors, not all. Every summary is labeled AI-generated and links
        to the original — please verify anything important against the source. Preprints are labeled
        as not peer-reviewed.
      </p>
    </section>
    <section>
      <h2>Copyright</h2>
      <p>
        Only open-access papers are included, always with attribution and license. PDFs are hosted
        only when the license permits redistribution; otherwise we link to the original.
      </p>
    </section>
  </div>
</Base>
